message.text:
𝐖𝐞𝐥𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐭𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐒𝐤𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐅𝐄𝐔 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐞 𝐘 𝐂𝐥𝐮𝐛! 🧡🍃♾️

We are beyond excited to welcome our new Y’ers on board as we rise together toward greater leadership, creativity, and impact on our campus community.🌟

Your journey begins here! Filled with opportunities to grow through leadership programs, advocacy projects, and events. 

This is your chance to showcase your talents, share your passions, and build meaningful friendships with fellow Y’ers who will make this year truly unforgettable.

Together, let’s make this academic year not only memorable but also inspiring and impactful for everyone. Here’s to flying higher and brighter with CYC!🎈🌟

#CYCibolSaHimPAMPawid
#DefyingLimits
#TheLegaCYContinues
#CYC27
#TamHunt2025 

Caption by Alexine Medenilla
Publication Material by Angela Courtney Reynoso

Applicable to psychology, business, medicine (ex. biology, nursing, medtech, etc.), engineering, culinary, and more.

New sched (regular days of classes):
Monday and Thursday : 2pm - 5pm
Wednesday and Saturday: 10am - 5pm

Errand fee: 35/person

At dahil time-consuming, magastos, at nakaka-drain ang pag-travel plus pagkain when going to certain places just to look for books, I'm here to lessen that burden.

If you ought to purchase physical books but can't find it in nearby bookshops, you can send me a message about the book/s you need and provide the details at hahanapin ko sya for you. The allotted time gives me the chance to contact/go to the publishing house/s for the price and availability of books. My replies will depend on my availability from classes.

Book price varies but with proof of price through purchase receipts. Cancellation is allowed but needs to inform me 1-2 days prior so I can process full refund, unless the book is already purchased. Mind Mover books are in b&w color scheme.

Same day payment and purchase is allowed but strictly no cancellations.

- Book name
- Book edition

- Author/s.

Meet up around FEU Main or along España.
Mode of payment: Cash or GCash (1 or 2 days before purchase) / Gcash on same day purchases.

Max of 2 books per person and 4 persons limit per day (except Wednesday, with 2 books/person, 6 persons limit) on regular days of classes.
